    "text_5": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "A Cinematic Finale: The Campaign and Lookbook",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The launch of Volume IV is accompanied by a stunning campaign film and lookbook, extending MANORS\u2019 collaboration with acclaimed director Douglas Guillot Supine, Cinematographer Ollie Allison, and photographer Jack Ducey. The campaign features MANORS\u2019 latest ambassador, Dylan Block, alongside James Wilson, Nathan Sampson, and Elizabeth Breed, as they explore the dramatic landscapes of Norway\u2019s northern coastline.</p><p>This visual narrative captures the essence of the Frontier Collection \u2013 a journey into the unknown, where the beauty of the landscape and the innovation of the apparel come together in perfect harmony. The dramatic fjords and rugged terrain of Lofoten Links are more than just a backdrop; they are a testament to the adventurous spirit that has defined MANORS from the very beginning.</p><p></p><h2><strong>Lofoten Links: The Ultimate Golf Adventure</strong></h2><p>Since its founding, Lofoten Links has been a dream destination for golfers, and it\u2019s easy to see why. Built into the rugged Norwegian landscape, this world-class course offers an experience like no other. It\u2019s a place where the natural world and the game of golf intersect in the most spectacular way possible.</p><p>The decision to shoot the final chapter of The Frontier Collection at Lofoten Links is a fitting conclusion to MANORS\u2019 journey. This course, with its wild surroundings and challenging layout, perfectly encapsulates the spirit of adventure and innovation that has driven MANORS from the start. As the brand prepares to release the final volume of its groundbreaking collection, it\u2019s clear that Lofoten Links is not just a location \u2013 it\u2019s a symbol of everything MANORS stands for.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
